{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-09",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_09_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "09 - The Mock Turtle's Story",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.768,
  "page_num": 1,
  "page_total": 4,
  "page_start_sec": 12.71,
  "page_end_sec": 255.2,
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 12.71,
      "end": 13.36,
      "text": "CHAPTER IX."
    },
    {
      "start": 13.36,
      "end": 13.36,
      "text": "You"
    },
    {
      "start": 14.208,
      "end": 16.84,
      "text": "can't think how glad I am to see you again,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 17.04,
      "end": 18.04,
      "text": "you dear old thing!"
    },
    {
      "start": 18.28,
      "end": 21.94,
      "text": "said the Duchess, as she tucked her arm affectionately into Alice's,"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.02,
      "end": 22.64,
      "text": "and they walked"
    },
    {
      "start": 22.64,
      "end": 23.14,
      "text": "off together."
    },
    {
      "start": 24.288,
      "end": 27.0,
      "text": "Alice was very glad to find her in such a pleasant temper,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 27.12,
      "end": 28.04,
      "text": "and thought to herself"
    },
    {
      "start": 28.34,
      "end": 30.76,
      "text": "that perhaps it was only the pepper that had"
    },
    {
      "start": 30.76,
      "end": 32.7,
      "text": "made her so savage when they met in the kitchen."
    },
    {
      "start": 33.7,
      "end": 34.6,
      "text": "When _I'm_ a Duchess,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 34.72,
      "end": 35.6,
      "text": "she said to herself,"
    },
    {
      "start": 35.88,
      "end": 37.22,
      "text": "not in a very hopeful tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.32,
      "end": 37.52,
      "text": "though,"
    },
    {
      "start": 37.98,
      "end": 40.54,
      "text": "I won't have any pepper in my kitchen _at all_."
    },
    {
      "start": 40.72,
      "end": 42.44,
      "text": "Soup does very well without--"
    },
    {
      "start": 43.424,
      "end": 44.2,
      "text": "Maybe it's always"
    },
    {
      "start": 44.3,
      "end": 46.2,
      "text": "pepper that makes people hot-tempered,"
    },
    {
      "start": 46.32,
      "end": 47.02,
      "text": "she went on,"
    },
    {
      "start": 47.08,
      "end": 49.34,
      "text": "very much pleased at having found out a new"
    },
    {
      "start": 49.42,
      "end": 49.96,
      "text": "kind of rule,"
    },
    {
      "start": 50.14,
      "end": 52.18,
      "text": "and vinegar that makes them sour--"
    },
    {
      "start": 52.82,
      "end": 54.34,
      "text": "and camomile that makes them bitter--"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.12,
      "end": 55.66,
      "text": "and barley"
    },
    {
      "start": 55.88,
      "end": 58.44,
      "text": "sugar and such things that make children sweet-tempered."
    },
    {
      "start": 58.92,
      "end": 60.36,
      "text": "I only wish people knew _that_:"
    },
    {
      "start": 60.62,
      "end": 62.46,
      "text": "then they wouldn't be so stingy about it,"
    },
    {
      "start": 62.52,
      "end": 62.72,
      "text": "you know."
    },
    {
      "start": 63.98,
      "end": 66.16,
      "text": "She had quite forgotten the Duchess by this time,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 66.3,
      "end": 68.32,
      "text": "and was a little startled when she heard"
    },
    {
      "start": 68.32,
      "end": 69.64,
      "text": "her voice close to her ear."
    },
    {
      "start": 70.528,
      "end": 71.68,
      "text": "You're thinking about something,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 71.84,
      "end": 72.26,
      "text": "my dear,"
    },
    {
      "start": 72.44,
      "end": 73.38,
      "text": "and that makes you"
    },
    {
      "start": 73.42,
      "end": 74.24,
      "text": "forget to talk."
    },
    {
      "start": 74.8,
      "end": 77.46,
      "text": "I can't tell you just now what the moral of that is,"
    },
    {
      "start": 77.68,
      "end": 78.82,
      "text": "but I shall remember it"
    },
    {
      "start": 78.98,
      "end": 79.23,
      "text": "in a bit."
    },
    {
      "start": 80.512,
      "end": 81.42,
      "text": "Perhaps it hasn't one,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 81.66,
      "end": 82.9,
      "text": "Alice ventured to remark."
    },
    {
      "start": 83.36,
      "end": 83.86,
      "text": "Tut,"
    },
    {
      "start": 83.92,
      "end": 84.22,
      "text": "tut,"
    },
    {
      "start": 84.26,
      "end": 84.64,
      "text": "child!"
    },
    {
      "start": 85.0,
      "end": 85.92,
      "text": "said the Duchess."
    },
    {
      "start": 86.4,
      "end": 87.46,
      "text": "Every thing's got a moral,"
    },
    {
      "start": 88.04,
      "end": 89.32,
      "text": "if only you can find it."
    },
    {
      "start": 89.98,
      "end": 92.26,
      "text": "And she squeezed herself up closer to Alice's"
    },
    {
      "start": 92.36,
      "end": 93.2,
      "text": "side as she spoke."
    },
    {
      "start": 94.72,
      "end": 97.28,
      "text": "Alice did not much like her keeping so close to her:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 97.4,
      "end": 98.86,
      "text": "first, because the Duchess"
    },
    {
      "start": 98.86,
      "end": 99.86,
      "text": "was _very_ ugly;"
    },
    {
      "start": 100.02,
      "end": 102.16,
      "text": "and secondly, because she was exactly"
    },
    {
      "start": 102.16,
      "end": 103.86,
      "text": "the right height to rest her chin on"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.2,
      "end": 104.62,
      "text": "Alice's shoulder,"
    },
    {
      "start": 104.78,
      "end": 106.8,
      "text": "and it was an uncomfortably sharp chin."
    },
    {
      "start": 107.25,
      "end": 107.8,
      "text": "However,"
    },
    {
      "start": 108.02,
      "end": 109.34,
      "text": "she did not like to be rude,"
    },
    {
      "start": 109.54,
      "end": 111.1,
      "text": "so she bore it as well as she could."
    },
    {
      "start": 111.88,
      "end": 114.12,
      "text": "The game's going on rather better now,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 114.3,
      "end": 117.08,
      "text": "she said, by way of keeping up the conversation a little."
    },
    {
      "start": 118.336,
      "end": 120.06,
      "text": "\"'Tis so,\" said the Duchess:",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 120.08,
      "end": 121.58,
      "text": "and the moral of that is--"
    },
    {
      "start": 122.14,
      "end": 122.42,
      "text": "'Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 122.42,
      "end": 123.04,
      "text": "'tis love,"
    },
    {
      "start": 123.18,
      "end": 125.44,
      "text": "'tis love, that makes the world go round!'"
    },
    {
      "start": 126.368,
      "end": 128.26,
      "text": "Somebody said, Alice whispered,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 128.38,
      "end": 130.75,
      "text": "that it's done by everybody minding their own business!"
    },
    {
      "start": 131.48,
      "end": 132.28,
      "text": "Ah,"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.28,
      "end": 132.5,
      "text": "well!"
    },
    {
      "start": 132.62,
      "end": 134.26,
      "text": "It means much the same thing,"
    },
    {
      "start": 134.56,
      "end": 135.6,
      "text": "said the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 135.6,
      "end": 138.8,
      "text": "digging her sharp little chin into Alice's shoulder as she added,"
    },
    {
      "start": 139.26,
      "end": 140.64,
      "text": "and the moral of _that_ is--"
    },
    {
      "start": 141.28,
      "end": 142.56,
      "text": "'Take care of the sense,"
    },
    {
      "start": 142.62,
      "end": 144.66,
      "text": "and the sounds will take care of themselves.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 145.84,
      "end": 148.54,
      "text": "How fond she is of finding morals in things!",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 148.78,
      "end": 149.78,
      "text": "Alice thought to herself."
    },
    {
      "start": 151.18,
      "end": 154.84,
      "text": "I dare say you're wondering why I don't put my arm round your waist,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 155.08,
      "end": 156.76,
      "text": "the Duchess said after a pause:"
    },
    {
      "start": 157.07,
      "end": 161.72,
      "text": "the reason is, that I'm doubtful about the temper of your flamingo."
    },
    {
      "start": 162.14,
      "end": 163.26,
      "text": "Shall I try the experiment?"
    },
    {
      "start": 164.26,
      "end": 165.7,
      "text": "He might bite,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 165.96,
      "end": 167.42,
      "text": "Alice cautiously replied,"
    },
    {
      "start": 167.7,
      "end": 170.36,
      "text": "not feeling at all anxious to have the experiment tried."
    },
    {
      "start": 171.488,
      "end": 171.94,
      "text": "Very true,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 172.28,
      "end": 173.22,
      "text": "said the Duchess:"
    },
    {
      "start": 173.824,
      "end": 175.64,
      "text": "flamingoes and mustard both bite."
    },
    {
      "start": 175.78,
      "end": 177.72,
      "text": "And the moral of that is--"
    },
    {
      "start": 177.88,
      "end": 179.86,
      "text": "'Birds of a feather flock together.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 181.504,
      "end": 182.98,
      "text": "Only mustard isn't a bird,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 183.2,
      "end": 184.22,
      "text": "Alice remarked."
    },
    {
      "start": 185.024,
      "end": 185.84,
      "text": "Right, as usual,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 186.04,
      "end": 186.82,
      "text": "said the Duchess."
    },
    {
      "start": 186.98,
      "end": 189.39,
      "text": "what a clear way you have of putting things!"
    },
    {
      "start": 190.72,
      "end": 191.28,
      "text": "It's a mineral,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 191.38,
      "end": 192.52,
      "text": "I _think_, said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 193.24,
      "end": 195.04,
      "text": "Of course it is, said the Duchess,"
    },
    {
      "start": 195.12,
      "end": 197.68,
      "text": "who seemed ready to agree to everything that Alice said:"
    },
    {
      "start": 198.432,
      "end": 200.2,
      "text": "there's a large mustard-mine near here."
    },
    {
      "start": 200.72,
      "end": 202.1,
      "text": "And the moral of that is--"
    },
    {
      "start": 202.38,
      "end": 203.6,
      "text": "'The more there is of mine,"
    },
    {
      "start": 203.82,
      "end": 205.35,
      "text": "the less there is of yours.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 205.64,
      "end": 206.52,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 206.52,
      "end": 207.8,
      "text": "I know! exclaimed Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 208.0,
      "end": 209.74,
      "text": "who had not attended to this last remark."
    },
    {
      "start": 210.496,
      "end": 211.01,
      "text": "It's a vegetable."
    },
    {
      "start": 211.42,
      "end": 212.64,
      "text": "It doesn't look like one,"
    },
    {
      "start": 212.7,
      "end": 213.39,
      "text": "but it is."
    },
    {
      "start": 214.42,
      "end": 216.52,
      "text": "I quite agree with you, said the Duchess;",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 216.96,
      "end": 218.5,
      "text": "and the moral of that is--"
    },
    {
      "start": 219.42,
      "end": 220.82,
      "text": "'Be what you would seem to be'--",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 221.3,
      "end": 222.78,
      "text": "or if you'd like it put more simply--"
    },
    {
      "start": 223.5,
      "end": 226.22,
      "text": "'Never imagine yourself not to be otherwise than"
    },
    {
      "start": 226.22,
      "end": 228.78,
      "text": "what it might appear to others that what you were"
    },
    {
      "start": 228.98,
      "end": 231.38,
      "text": "or might have been was not otherwise than what"
    },
    {
      "start": 231.38,
      "end": 233.66,
      "text": "you had been would have appeared to them to be"
    },
    {
      "start": 233.8,
      "end": 234.14,
      "text": "otherwise.'"
    },
    {
      "start": 235.01,
      "end": 237.26,
      "text": "I think I should understand that better,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 237.52,
      "end": 238.84,
      "text": "Alice said very politely,"
    },
    {
      "start": 239.36,
      "end": 240.48,
      "text": "if I had it written down:"
    },
    {
      "start": 240.94,
      "end": 242.74,
      "text": "but I can't quite follow it as you say it."
    },
    {
      "start": 243.776,
      "end": 245.62,
      "text": "That's nothing to what I could say if I",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 245.62,
      "end": 248.16,
      "text": "chose, the Duchess replied, in a pleased tone."
    },
    {
      "start": 249.024,
      "end": 250.42,
      "text": "Pray don't trouble yourself to say",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 250.42,
      "end": 252.06,
      "text": "it any longer than that, said Alice."
    },
    {
      "start": 252.68,
      "end": 253.02,
      "text": "Oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 253.02,
      "end": 255.2,
      "text": "don't talk about trouble! said the Duchess."
    }
  ]
}
